                                                                                                                                                     Shane Bond in line for Lanka tour
    Christchurch: Shane Bond is likely to end his 18-month exile from international cricket with New Zealand rsquo;s tour of Sri Lanka in August after snapping ties with the lsquo;rebel rsquo; Indian Cricket League. New Zealand Cricket chief executive Justin Vaughan said he has received legal notification from Bond along with that of Daryl Tuffey rsquo;s and Craig McMillan rsquo;s that they have officially severed ties with the ICL.
    ldquo;I can confirm that NZC has received communication from the legal representatives of Daryl Tuffey, Craig McMillan and Shane Bond and documentation indicated those three players have terminated their contracts with the ICL, rdquo; Vaughan was quoted as saying by a newspaper.
    ICL issue
    Dhaka: Seven more Bangladeshi cricketers, aligned to Indian Cricket League (ICL), have filed applications to return to the official fold, leaving only two players from the country with the lsquo;rebel rsquo; league. Shahriar Nafees, Aftab Ahmed, Alok Kapali, Nazimuddin, Mohammad Sharif, Farhad Reza and Golam Mabud submitted lsquo;letters of intent rsquo; at the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) a week ahead of the deadline. The BCB has decided to allow Bangladeshi cricketers aligned with the ICL to participate in domestic cricket subject to the termination of their contract with the rebel league by June 15.
    Bagan win
    Calcutta: Mohun Bagan beat Eastern Railways by 93 runs in a semi-final match of the CAB knockout tournament on Sunday. Arindam Das of Bagan scored 118.
  BRIEF SCORES
  Mohun Bagan 307/3 (Arindam Das 118, Wriddhiman Saha 73 n.o., Debratra Das 93 n.o.). Eastern Railways 214/5 (Prasenjit Das 104; Ashrafuddin 2/25, Sougata Datta 2/41). Mohun Bagan won by 93 runs.
    ICFD meet
    Lucknow: In a first of its kind, the Indian Cricket Federation for Disabled (ICFD) will be organising a national-level cricket tournament for people with physical disabilities by the end of this year. ldquo;We are in the process of framing a new cricket calendar for the year under which zonal cricket tournaments for the disabled in all age groups shall be organised round the year, rdquo; said ICFD founder secretary A.W. Siddiqui. 
